TITLE: Initializing a Zero Copy Account with init Constraint in Rust
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to initialize a zero-copy account using the init constraint. It shows the account structure and the implementation of the initialize function using load_init to set initial data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/solana-foundation/anchor/blob/master/docs/content/docs/features/zero-copy.mdx#2025-04-18_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
#[derive(Accounts)]
pub struct Initialize<'info> {
    #[account(
        init,
        // 10240 bytes is max space to allocate with init constraint
        space = 8 + 10232,
        payer = payer,
    )]
    pub data_account: AccountLoader<'info, Data>,
    #[account(mut)]
    pub payer: Signer<'info>,
    pub system_program: Program<'info, System>,
}

pub fn initialize(ctx: Context<Initialize>) -> Result<()> {
    let account = &mut ctx.accounts.data_account.load_init()?;
    account.data = [1; 10232];
    Ok(())
}
```

